HEADWORD: Saligenin
<hw>Sa*lig"e*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sal</ets>icin + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A phenol alcohol obtained, by the decomposition of salicin, as a
white crystalline substance; -- called also <altname>hydroxy-benzyl
alcohol</altname>.</def> <-- ortho-hydroxybenzyl alcohol, saligenol,
salicyl alcohol. <chform>HOCH2.C6H4.OH</chform> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

